                <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 59.</note>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Received 9.50 a. m., August 13, 1870.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. E. B. Washburne</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Fish</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-08-12">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">August 12, 1870.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Fish,</hi>
                    <hi rend="italic">Washington:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>French government decides North Germans, with certain exceptions, quit France.
                    Advise Prussian government and instruct me. Impossible for great numbers of poor
                    to leave without pecuniary aid.</p>
                <p>Will Prussian government place a credit at my disposition to assist poor in
                    leaving? It seems necessary in the interest of humanity.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WASHBURNE, <hi rend="italic">Paris.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
